description: This code lets admins edit processing orders and lets customers effectively “edit” a processing order from My Account. It adds an Edit Order action that uses WooCommerce’s Order Again flow to refill the cart with the old order’s items, stores the original order ID in the session, and when the new checkout completes it links the two orders with notes and automatically cancels the original. In short, customers edit by creating a replacement order; the old order is cancelled and both orders cross-reference each other.

This adds a “Request account deletion” button to the My Account → Edit Account page for logged-in users. This snippet adds a small product thumbnail next to each line item on the customer’s My Account → Orders → View order page. It hooks into woocommerce_order_item_name, checks that we’re on the view-order endpoint, fetches the item’s product image at 100×100, and prepends it (floated left) before the item name. If a product has no image, nothing changes. It doesn’t affect the cart, checkout, admin, or emails.
